            <p>
                Descovrir uses a color scheme derived from <a href="http://boronine.com/husl/">HUSLp</a>, which corrects issues with HSL, CIE-based color schemes, and HUSL itself at the price of highly saturated colors.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Hue</strong>. 5 primary hues are used by Descovrir.
            </p>

            <ul>
                <li>
                    9&deg; &ndash; Red. Reserved for errors, danger, major issues, or to provide warmth.
                </li>
                <li>
                    81&deg; &ndash; Gold. Serves as the base hue. Useful for warning states. Where possible use this hue over red.
                </li>
                <li>
                    153&deg; &ndash; Green. Useful for success and acceptance states.
                </li>
                <li>
                    225&deg; &ndash; Blue. Indicates a clickable element or navigation element. Also an accent color when no other is applicable.
                </li>
                <li>
                    297&deg; &ndash; Purple. Represents authority and acceptance.
                </li>
            </ul>

            <p>
                Other hues can be used, particularly when hue is a linear function, such as a progress bar color.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Saturation</strong>. Descovrir defaults to using the full saturation available (100%) at any particular hue. Desaturation is available particularly at disabled states, and multiple of 20% are preferred for such states.
            </p>

            <p>
                <strong>Lightness</strong>. Any lightness values may be used. Descovrir recommends against values darker than 20%. Default to 20%, 43%, 66%, 78%, 90%, 95%, and 99% where applicable.
            </p>

