    <h2>11. Page Layouts</h2>

        <h3>11.1 Basic Page Layout</h3>

            <p>
                Most pages on Descovrir are limited to a menu icon, a title, body contents, and end in linear navigation. This simplicity forces focus on the task at hand.
            </p>

            <p>
                Set the body to <code>max-width-10</code>. Use an <code>h1</code> at the top. End with linear navigation and a menu element.
            </p>

        <h3>11.2 Navigated Page Layout</h3>

            <p>
                A page that has been intentionally navigated to includes breadcrumbs or other navigational feature where applicable.
            </p>

            <p>
                Before the <code>h1</code> of &sect;11.1, include breadcrumbs navigation. Alternatively, set the body to <code>aside-right-3</code>, and use vertical navigation in the <code>aside</code>.
            </p>

        <h3>11.3 Object Representation</h3>

            <p>
                Provide an overview of information about an object. Examples are a user profile, component statistics, or a history of changes.
            </p>

            <p>
                Start with <code>aside-left-4</code>. Include a <var>264x264</var> image at top top of the <code>aside</code>. The <code>main</code> element starts with an <code>h1</code>. Delegate concise, vital statistics and information to the <code>aside</code>, and primary content to the <code>main</code>.
            </p>

        <h3>11.4 Settings</h3>

            <p>
                Some views transverse Descovrir's sections (Learn, Contribute, Mentor...).
            </p>

            <p>
                Borrowing the &sect;11.1 Basic Page Layout, and add horizontal tabs across the top. Alternatively, set the body to <code>aside-right-3</code>, and use vertical navigation in the <code>aside</code>. Keep to a single column form.
            </p>

        <h3>11.5 Search, Sort, &amp; Filter</h3>

            <p>
                The search with filters layout is based on a simple aside layout.
            </p>

            <p>
                Set the body to <code>aside-right-3</code>, and use vertical navigation for filters in the <code>aside</code>. Include sorting options in the aside. Start the <code>main</code> element with an <code>h1</code> and possibly breadcrumbs. Then include a large search bar. Show a list with thumbnails in infinite scroll below the search bar. Manage empty states.
            </p>

    <h2>12. Concluding Remarks</h2>

        <h3>12.1 Extending with BEM</h3>

            <p>
